<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TPal8">
<l>vampaviḻ vāṉavar vāyuṟai vaḻaṅka māniti kapilaiyoṇ kaṇṇāṭi mutalā</l>
<l>vemperu māṉpaṭi makkalaṅ kāṇṭaṟ kēṟpaṉa vāyiṉa koṇṭunaṉ muṉivar</l>
<l>tumpuru nāratar pukuntaṉa rivarō tōṉṟiṉa ṉiraviyun tulaṅkoḷi parappi</l>
<l>yampara talattilniṉ ṟakalkiṉṟa tiruḷpō yaraṅkattam māpaḷḷi yeḻuntaru ḷāyē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>As the celestials offer fragrant Harialli grass,</l>
<l>the good sages, Tumburū, and Nārada have brought things suitable for our Lord to look at—</l>
<l rend="indent">beginning with great treasure-hoards, the Kapilā [cow], [and] a shiny mirror—</l>
<l>and entered [here], right?</l>
<l>The Sun too has appeared spreading bright light,</l>
<l>darkness is departing from the sky.</l>
<l>O Lord of Raṅgam, do grace to wake up from sleep!</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
